  "extractionNotes": "Extracted 7 rules from Section 3.2 Eligibility Criteria. Note: The minimum age is 18 in most provinces but 19 in BC, NB, NS, NL, NT, NU, YT — the base rule uses 18; provincial exceptions should be handled as separate rules or during normalization. Self-employed income calculation (2-year average) and employment duration (2 years continuous) are noted but require separate self-employment rules. The discretionary exception clause at the end ('at the sole discretion of the committee') was NOT converted into a rule as it is non-deterministic."
